about.summary: It is a complete suite to estimate models based on moment conditions. It includes the two step Generalized method of moments (Hansen 1982; <doi:10.2307/1912775>), the iterated GMM and continuous updated estimator (Hansen, Eaton and Yaron 1996; <doi:10.2307/1392442>) and several methods that belong to the Generalized Empirical Likelihood family of estimators (Smith 1997; <doi:10.1111/j.0013-0133.1997.174.x>, Kitamura 1997; <doi:10.1214/aos/1069362388>, Newey and Smith 2004; <doi:10.1111/j.1468-0262.2004.00482.x>, and Anatolyev 2005 <doi:10.1111/j.1468-0262.2005.00601.x>).

name: r-gmm
raw_recipe:
{% set version = '1.6-4' %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-gmm
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/gmm_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/gmm/gmm_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 03ad5ff37d174e9cef13fa41d866412c57b7cbd9155312831e16a1fcda70bc95

build:
  merge_build_host: True  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('fortran') }}        # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_fortran') }}  # [win]
    - {{posix}}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{posix}}make
    - {{posix}}sed               # [win]
    - {{posix}}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{posix}}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-sandwich
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{native}}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-sandwich

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('gmm')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('gmm')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://CRAN.R-project.org/package=gmm
  license: GPL-2
  summary: It is a complete suite to estimate models based on moment conditions. It includes
    the two step Generalized method of moments (Hansen 1982; <doi:10.2307/1912775>),
    the iterated GMM and continuous updated estimator (Hansen, Eaton and Yaron 1996;
    <doi:10.2307/1392442>) and several methods that belong to the Generalized Empirical
    Likelihood family of estimators (Smith 1997; <doi:10.1111/j.0013-0133.1997.174.x>,
    Kitamura 1997; <doi:10.1214/aos/1069362388>, Newey and Smith 2004; <doi:10.1111/j.1468-0262.2004.00482.x>,
    and Anatolyev 2005 <doi:10.1111/j.1468-0262.2005.00601.x>).
  license_family: GPL2
  license_file:
    - '{{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/GPL-2'

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
